Pulled BBQ Jackfruit Sandwiches
  --Candice Hutchings

"Meat"
2 cans young jackfruit
2 tsp cayenne pepper
2 tsp garlic powder
salt and pepper to taste
2 tbsp olive oil

In large bowl, combine jackfruit, cayenne, garlic powder, salt, and pepper, and stir until jackfruit is thoroughly covered. On medium high heat, drizzle olive oil into nonstick pan. Warm oil, then add jackfruit. Allow to simmer until jackfruit is tender.

Sauce:
1 c ketchup
1/4 c maple syrup
2 tbsp liquid smoke
1 tbsp shoyu
1 tbsp white vinegar
2 tbsp hot sauce

In a small bowl, combine all ingredients and whisk thoroughly. Pour half into pan with the jackfruit and let simmer for 15-20 min. With a potato masher or fork, mash the jackfruit until it begins to shred and resemble pulled pork. Remove from heat and combine with remaining bbq sauce.

Slaw:
1 bag shredded slaw mix
1 tbsp apple cider vinegar
1 tbsp olive oil 
pinch of salt
2 tsp garlic powder
2 tsp cayenne

In large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix.

Assembly:
4 hamburger buns

Spoon generous portion of jackfruit onto bun, top with slaw and serve.
